description:
&lt;p&gt;A&lt;strong&gt; Senior Health Care Assistant &lt;/strong&gt;is required by one of the UK’s largest NHS Hospital Trusts. Based at Southmead Hospital, you will be responsible for supporting the pain clinic team in providing care for patients suffering with chronic pain, within the pain theatre and pain clinic department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHY APPLY?&lt;/strong&gt; The Senior Health Care assistant position is a fantastic opportunity to take on a role with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as a team member within a nationally recognised Pain service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping to support patients with long term conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of some appropriate specialist roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And not to mention the opportunity to further develop your professional career path within one of the UK&#39;s largest NHS Trusts (£550m turnover and 7000+ staff), all whilst working with fantastic bunch of colleagues and making the world a better place working for the NHS!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt; As senior Health Care assistant, your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help to promote and maintain a clean and comfortable environment within the department and pain theatres.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contribute to accurate written and computerised documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assist in the admission, treatment and recovery of patients undergoing procedures in the pain clinic and theatre.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prepare clinics ensuring referral letters and any necessary documentation and equipment is made available.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blood sugar analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU:&lt;/strong&gt; The successful Senior health care assistant will have good experience:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NVQ LEVEL 3 in Health and Social care. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In the acute setting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatres or &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;outpatients&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
